    "body": "Heh, I suppose that engineer would be me.\n\nI have no case against the removal, but I can't see any real benefit in it either.\n\nFYI, my reasoning for always giving the option to disable (this happens quite often):\nI'm building a program/lib for an architecture where the binary I want builds fine, but compile borks on some other binary that the upstream devs decide is super-mega-important (it's not). Now I have to patch my build to work-around.\n\nGranted that's not likely to happen here. Just explaining the logic.\n\nACK if others agree, but that doesn't mean I like it :)\n",
